                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39253",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "My bet is that this is a PHP bug (and\/or intended feature). Have you tried writing to php:\/\/stderr directly? I suspect that it behaves differently than trigger_error().\r\n\r\nIf you can confirm that it behaves differently (i.e., writing to php:\/\/stderr and trigger_error write to different locations when directly invoked), you should log your issue upstream to the PHP project. If it does not -- i.e., if writing to php:\/\/stderr directly actually writes to your vhost's error log like trigger_error does -- then and only then would I consider this a ZF issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-15T13:56:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-15T13:56:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
